snippet.textDisplay:
These teasers do nothing for me. All I see is the embarrassing disgrace this trilogy has been, and how desperate you guys are to stop revising your opening weekend box office projections down again and again.

Disney, when you do your post mortem on why this film under-performed at the box office, know that I would have bought at least one ticket if you hadn't let your employees at lucasfilm gleefully attack the fans in public. Calling them every hateful thing under the sun all because they dared to say that they weren't into your movie was disgusting, and made me realize that the folks you left in charge of this franchise are not just creatively bankrupt; they're also a bunch of immoral cowards who gladly wield the massive power they gain being attached to your brand to crush individuals.

Disney, until you do something to make it up to the fans for your employees' awful behavior, you won't get one cent from me. Not for your shows, not for your merch, not for your parks. Not. One. Cent.
